## 🔍 Requirements Quality Checklist

Before finalizing requirements, validate:

### Response Safety Checks (Blocking)
- [ ] Naming authority check passed: plan/report references use `feature-file-name + scenario-name` canonical formula
- [ ] Status/phase mutation check passed: no lifecycle metadata changed unless explicitly requested
- [ ] Style parity check passed: output matches existing target `.feature` file style
- [ ] BDD purity check passed: acceptance criteria are behavior-focused and implementation-agnostic
- [ ] Scope check passed: no unrequested governance/process edits included

### Gherkin Quality
- [ ] All scenarios use Given-When-Then format
- [ ] Each scenario tests one specific behavior
- [ ] Given clauses describe initial state (no actions)
- [ ] When clauses describe actions (no outcomes)
- [ ] Then clauses describe observable outcomes (no actions)
- [ ] Scenarios are technology-agnostic (no implementation details)
- [ ] Examples provided for parameterized scenarios

### Acceptance Criteria Quality
- [ ] Each criterion is specific and testable
- [ ] Criteria include both functional and non-functional requirements
- [ ] Verification outcomes are observable and measurable in behavior terms
- [ ] Performance and security criteria included where applicable

### Architecture Alignment
- [ ] All scenarios map to architecture patterns
- [ ] Out-of-scope dependencies identified with mock strategy
- [ ] Database schema compatibility verified
- [ ] API security requirements defined
- [ ] UI/UX patterns specified

### Completeness
- [ ] Happy path scenarios defined
- [ ] Edge cases identified
- [ ] Error scenarios covered
- [ ] Subscription tier variations addressed
- [ ] Performance requirements specified
- [ ] Security requirements explicit

