## 🎯 Success Criteria

Requirements generation is successful when:

- [ ] All scenarios follow Given-When-Then format correctly
- [ ] Each scenario has 3-5 testable acceptance criteria
- [ ] Out-of-scope dependencies identified with mock strategy
- [ ] Architecture patterns mapped to implementation
- [ ] Edge cases and error scenarios covered
- [ ] Scenario set is complete for full feature behavior coverage
- [ ] No ambiguities requiring clarification
- [ ] Stakeholder can understand requirements without technical knowledge
- [ ] Developer can implement without asking clarification questions
- [ ] Planning phase can derive test design from acceptance criteria without rewriting requirements

